<P>
A teen-age British girl pleaded not guilty Tuesday before a juvenile court to 
charges of heroin smuggling. 
</P>
<P>
Patricia Cahill, 17, and a friend, Karyn Smith, 19, were arrested in July on 
charges of possessing 58 pounds of heroin, which police said they were trying 
to smuggle inside liquid-soap bottles. 
</P>
<P>
If found guilty, Cahill could get a life sentence. Smith has pleaded guilty and 
asked for mercy. 
</P>
